Yesterday i went to the Red Cross to give blood since they have called me 2x. So I went done the questions ( as strange as they where ) did the iron testing everything was fine so  go get set up to donate. The tech had trouble finding a good vein b/c I have small ones so she had to have help. ( bet you can see where this is going allready ) So the needle goes in everything seems fine till I get dizzy and the vein slows down. They lay me down, ask if  i still wanna donate I said yes, so they reposition the needle, which hurt! Then it starts going good again but I go pale and feel even more light headed/dizzy and the blood flow slows down again. The tech ended up pulling the line b/c she said it wasnt worth be getting any worse to donate :( I was upset/embarrassed/frustrated. Upset b/c I wasnt able to donate and they needed my blood type. Embarrssed b/c those who were in there donated where watching me I guess there was nothing else to do lol and frustrated b/c i had went through all that and they ended up tossing the bag since it wasnt full and couldnt use it. I got cheered up when a guy that was in there donating said " that little girl is my hero" I smiled and thought "little gir?" what am I  a 7yr old. I ended up staying an extra 45min or so b/c they wanted to keep an eye on me to make sure I was ok. Everyone kept asking me if i had ate/drank that day and the day b4 I said I had. I think what happen was I am on the end of my cycle and well you get the idea.  Spent the rest of the day tired/groogy w/ JB forceing water in me. Today my arm is swore but i am thinking i cant wait till June 1st so i can donate again lol! This was the 2nd time i had donated Jb goes all the time but i was Iffy b/c i have been anemic in the past, the tech said she was suprised I had passed my iron test b/c I looked pale when I came in. I thought nope I am naturly this white-- have very fair skin like most people w/ red hair.

BUT I did have a cute Alexander Moment wednesday that I just have to share. We took him to school he walked into his classroom and said " this is my mommy" everyone started smileing and laughing it was so great!
